{
  "doc_id": "5321",
  "text": "Studies of specific fisheries seeking the MSC label show that consumers are willing to pay a higher price for pollock (France) [CITATION_1] and lobster (U.S.) [CITATION_2] . Brécard et al. [CITATION_3] find that French and Belgian consumers are familiar with fish eco-labels and that the harvesting process (wild vs. farmed) and the price are factors influencing the decision to buy. Surveys indicated that when price increases, consumers are less likely to choose eco-labeled products [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . Roheim et al. [CITATION_7] show a higher consumer demand and a 14.2% price premium on MSC-labeled processed frozen pollock than non-MSC fish products in the U.K. marketplace.",
